  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Ninjutsu (Suiton)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 5</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 5</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 19 | <b>Successes:</b> 3</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 7 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 19</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> H, F</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>A technique that builds on the Maboroshi Senbon Ame technique, the user creates clouds from the water vapor in the air which rain needles created from the water. The user of this technique creates a burst of clouds centered on himself that rain Senbon formed from the water. Any hostile creature caught in the burst takes 2d6 damage every round it stays there, and may spend an additional point of chakra to increase the damage by +1d6 (maximum 6d6). In addition to hostile creatures taking damage every round they are in the burst, the burst increases by 5 ft. every round.<br><br>This technique cannot be performed in dry climates (such as dessert), though it will still work on a dry day.<br><br>Material Focus -Either nearby clouds, a humid environment or 5 liters or more of water.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Requires:</b> Maboroshi Senbon Ame (t)</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
